HEADWORD: Sensationalist
<hw>Sen*sa"tion*al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>An advocate of, or believer in, philosophical
sensationalism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who practices sensational writing or
speaking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

